oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo postcard of Pvt. Murray L. Austin in France
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Murray L. Austin of Scotts Hill, Tennessee was an ambulance driver in Transport Co. 306 for a field hospital in France during World War I. He posed in this photograph in front of a cathedral with a soldier with the surname Burke. He moved to Lexington after the war and became a postman. The photographer was L. Brochery of Le Mans, France. [See also GWjack001-GWjack010.]
